<item>
            <title>[LU-1832] double list add in ldlm</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1832</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When kernel has CONFIG_DEBUG_LIST on, there are some warnings about double list add in ldlm code. It is because ldlm_granted_list_add_lock() may add a lock to its own places. It is ok to do so but it is better to change code to suppress such warnings so we can use CONFIG_DEBUG_LIST to detect other bugs. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
